 extensive police files on the group, this book overcomes the scarcity of high-quality data that has beset the study of terrorism for decades. The book advances a multicausal and multilevel understanding of involvement in European homegrown jihadism. It stresses that the factors that initiate involvement are separate from those that sustain it, which in turn are again likely to differ from those that bring some individuals to actual acts of terrorism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aTerrorismzEuropevCase studies. 0aTerrorismzEuropexHistoryy21st century. 0aTerrorismzNetherlandsvCase studies. 0aTerrorismzNetherlandsxHistoryy21st century. 0aTerroristszEuropexHistoryy21st century. 0aTerroristszEurope. 0aTerroristszNetherlandsxHistoryy21st century. 0aTerroristszNetherlands. 4aReligion and Theology. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  aCauses.  aEurope.  aHofstadgroup.  aHomegrown jihadism.  aTerrorism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060672008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060401608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW0 cprintz978946298693040uhttps